        {
            "id": "3836c877ac8b4e75b2ecc",
            "questionText": "A hospital receives a shipment of I-131 with an initial activity of 50 mCi and a half-life of 8 days. Using the formula $!$A = A_0 e^{-\\lambda t}$!$ and first computing the decay constant $!$\\lambda$!$ based on the half-life, determine the activity $!$A$!$ of the I-131 sample after 24 days.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "bd6534fefda143ae81dad",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the relationship between the decay constant and the half-life. Which formula correctly expresses the decay constant $!$\\lambda$!$ in terms of the half-life $!$T_{1/2}$!$? Please choose the appropriate option.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "4a96e678-9acd-4cc8-8563-b2cf4e679b6d"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = \\frac{ln2}{T_{1/2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = T_{1/2} \\cdot ln2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = \\frac{T_{1/2}}{ln2}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "0346e8bad83d4bf49240d",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now that you have the expression for $!$\\lambda$!$, move on to the exponential decay law. Which formula correctly relates the current activity $!$A$!$, the initial activity $!$A_0$!$, the decay constant $!$\\lambda$!$, and time $!$t$!$?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "25c877b8-9a98-41c4-9844-addf85fe40a5"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 e^{-\\lambda t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 (1 - \\lambda t)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 e^{\\lambda t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "809ef8619fff423aa4117",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the product $!$\\lambda t$!$ using the decay constant expression from step 1 and the time $!$t = 24$!$ days (with the half-life being 8 days). What numerical value do you obtain for $!$\\lambda t$!$?",
